China Likely to Ease Money Policy, Journal Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-07T01:23:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/china-likely-to-ease-money-policy-journal-says-correct-.html
China ’s central bank may ease its
monetary policy by a “certain amount” in the next several months
adding cash to the market by buying bills from banks in open
market operations or cutting the required reserve ratio for
banks, China Securities Journal said a commentary today, written
by Zhang Zhaohui, a reporter at the newspaper.  Capital inflows to China may slow, boosting expectations
that reserve ratios will be lowered, Zhang wrote in the
newspaper.  Inflation may drop, reducing the need for reserve ratio
increases, Zhang said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  